## Module 2: Advanced AIOps — Vector Search & LLM RCA

### Learning Objectives
- ✓ Containerize an AI/ML application using Docker
- ✓ Upgrade from keyword matching to semantic vector search
- ✓ Integrate an LLM for automated Root Cause Analysis
- ✓ Understand embeddings, similarity search, and vector databases

### Core Topics
- Why keyword search fails for incident matching
- Sentence-Transformers: converting text to vectors
- ChromaDB: storing and querying embeddings locally
- LLM integration: sending context + query → receiving structured RCA
- Prompt engineering for operations (system prompts for incident analysis)
- Cost awareness: tokens, rate limits, caching

### Docker Lab
Write a Dockerfile for the AIOps assistant. Build and run the container. Verify the Streamlit app works inside Docker at `localhost:8501`.

### Vector Search Lab
Replace Jaccard similarity with ChromaDB. Ingest 50+ incident records as embeddings. Query: "database connection pool exhausted" and compare results vs keyword search.

### LLM RCA Lab
Connect to OpenAI/Anthropic API. Feed top 3 vector-matched incidents + current alert → LLM generates Root Cause Analysis with suggested fix.

### Break / Fix Activity
Inject a new incident log that has never been seen before. Observe how vector search finds semantically similar past incidents even without exact keyword match. Compare LLM RCA quality with and without context.

