## Module 4: Production Ops — CI/CD, Testing & Scaling

### Learning Objectives
- ✓ Build a CI/CD pipeline for AI/ML applications using GitHub Actions
- ✓ Write automated tests for ML and LLM-adjacent components
- ✓ Set up basic monitoring for production workloads
- ✓ Configure autoscaling for AI workloads

### Core Topics
- CI/CD fundamentals: build → test → deploy pipeline
- Testing AI/ML: unit tests, integration tests, golden dataset tests
- Monitoring basics: health checks, resource visibility
- Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) for K8s
- Deployment strategies: rolling update, blue-green, canary
- DORA metrics introduction (Deployment Frequency, Lead Time, CFR, MTTR)

### CI/CD Lab
Create a GitHub Actions workflow: on push → lint → run unit tests → build Docker image → push to registry. Add a manual approval gate for production deployment.

### Testing Lab
Write 5 automated tests: 2 unit tests (text chunking, embedding generation), 2 integration tests (API endpoint, DB query), 1 ML accuracy test (golden dataset of 10 known incidents).

### Autoscaling Lab
Configure HPA: scale pods from 2 → 5 when CPU exceeds 70%. Generate synthetic load using `hey` or `wrk`. Watch pods scale up and down.

### Break / Fix Activity
Push a broken test to the pipeline — observe CI failure and blocked deployment. Fix the test, push again, verify green pipeline. Simulate traffic spike and watch autoscaler respond.

